Linux
 
File handing basic 
#ls -listing file 
#cd foldername  -> change directory
#cd /           --> rootnodes tree structure
#pwd             --> print working directory

two types of path --  relative path , absolute path 

#mkdir Rohan  ----make directory name  
#touch 1.txt  ----> create blank file
#mv 1.txt this/ --> move file one to another
#cp 1.txt this/ --> copy file one to another
#cp /home/1.txt /home/harry2/
# pwd 

User in linux?
1) $ Regular user --> home directory
2) # Root user or super user --> Full access, user admin, sudo 
3) service user have own account (apache2)

Absolute vs Relative path
 
          / -> root node 
  bin     etc     apps 
f1  f0

cd fo2  --> relative path
cd /bin/f02  ---> Absolute path

# sudo apt-get update  -> apt - software install only update
# sudo apt-get upgrade ---> upgrade install the whole software
